{
  "text": "Theorem 2.6 ( [CITATION_1] ). There exists a unique admissible Borel structure on E \u03c6 . Furthermore, let \u03b1 be an E 0 -semigroup with product system F , and suppose \u03b1 is a minimal dilation of \u03c6. Then there is a canonical product system isomorphism \u03c8 : E \u03c6 \u2192 F .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119852954"
